def _get_time_bins(self, ax):
        if not isinstance(ax, pd.DatetimeIndex):
            raise TypeError(
                "axis must be a DatetimeIndex, but got "
                f"an instance of {type(ax).__name__}"
            )
    
        if len(ax) == 0:
            binner = labels = pd.DatetimeIndex(data=[], freq=self.freq, name=ax.name)
            return binner, [], labels

        adjusted_freq = pd.offsets.Day(self.freq.n, normalize=True)
        first = ax.min().floor(adjusted_freq)
        last = ax.max().ceil(adjusted_freq)

        binner = pd.date_range(start=first, end=last, freq=adjusted_freq, tz=ax.tz, name=ax.name)
        ax_values = ax.astype(np.int64)
        
        # Adjust bin edges based on the adjusted indices of the bins
        bin_edges = np.concatenate([binner[0:1].asi8 - (adjusted_freq.n * np.timedelta64(1, 'D')), binner[1:].asi8])
